snippet.textDisplay: Mechanically separated meat is one of two things. Either where they scrape absolutely every last piece of chicken they can off the bones using machines or it's where the carcass is put through some kind of process where it puree'd and run through a sieve to get every last scrap of anything that might be edible (not entirely sure of the details of this process), creating crap that goes into low grade meat products like hotdogs. Mechanically seperated beef and lamb is banned in many countries as not being fit for human consumption and those animals which are allowed aren't allowed to be labelled simply as being meat (and can't count towards the meat content of something).
